reviews.review: The movie was great. Everything you'd expect from the final installment of a franchise.
Loved this movie, I believe it was a good ending to the saga.

2 1/2 hours long and i was not entertained for one single second. it must be hard work to make a movie that bad. keep in mind, i LIKED the Last Jedi, which a lot of people didn't. i defended it's choices. there's nothing to defend here. the script was disjointed and could've been written by toddlers. the acting was... fine... but no performance could've saved it. the storyline tried to copy the mission-to-mission feel of the Return of the Jedi, but their goals fell somewhere between predictable and flat-out stupid. maybe idiot-Disney-execs had a heavy hand in its creative direction, or maybe JJ Abrams decided he was rich enough and just mailed it in, BUT they did accomplish one special feat in that the final conclusion to this long-running, much-loved series was objectively worse than what the Game of Thrones people put out. and for that, i will slow-clap JJ into my "never-watch-anything-he-makes-again" bin of directors.

So there are problems with this movie. There are dumb things like the animals storming the destroyer, there are a TON of rushed moments. The force power levels are all over the place. They spend time in extra areas that they don’t need to, and they gloss over important details. That said this FEELS LIKE STAR WARS! 8 was a massive misstep for the whole franchise. It may have been a well made movie, but it had huge plot holes, tons of dumb moments, ruined certain characters, discards things set up in 7 and doesn’t build towards a conclusion. It’s basically a stand alone movie happening in the middle of a trilogy. So 9 has to spend the first part of the movie throwing away all of the crap from 8 (like Rose, the worst character in all of Star Wars including jar jar), then set up a finale and execute it. Abrams captures the feel of Star Wars has a cool set up for the finale and executes it decently well. I felt like I was watching Star Wars and that is something 8 didn’t do at all. So as a die hard fan who grew up on it, I am willing to forgive a lot of little dumb things because overall this movie is so fun. Love it. (I wish they would remake the whole saga now going 1-6 and actually take the time and do it right, but right now I still don’t trust Disney to not ABSOLUTELY ruin Star Wars if they did that)
great way to wrap it up
It definitely serves to fix the mess of the Last Jedi and is more respectful of the Star Wars universe and Jedi spirit.

Like a droid, this movie was programmed to entertain, evoke nostalgia and plant the epic cap on the saga's end based on very rigid and safe algorithms.  Also like a droid: the film is a bit soulless, clunky, ill-paced, has robotic humor and communicates calculated plot points that don't seem to encapsulate emotionally charged story arcs.  I really wanted to like it more.
